**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<item instructions>
/ 1 = "<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%>Words representing the categories at the top will appear one-by-one in the middle of the screen. When the item belongs to a category on the left, press the left <%expressions.buttoninstruct2%>; when the item belongs to a category on the right, press the right <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%>. Items belong to only one category. If you make an error, an X will appear - fix the error by hitting the other <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%>.

This is a timed sorting task. GO AS FAST AS YOU CAN while making as few mistakes as possible. Going too slow or making too many errors will result in an uninterpretable score. This task will take about 5 minutes to complete."
/ 2 = "See above, the categories have changed. The items for sorting have changed as well. The rules are essentially the same. However, the categories will randomly switch their screen positions from trial to trial. Pay attention to the ordering at the beginning of each trial and respond accordingly.

When the item belongs to a category on the left, press the left (E) <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%> ; when the item belongs to a category on the right, press the right (I) <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%>. Items belong to only one category. An X appears after an error - fix the error by hitting the other <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%>. GO AS FAST AS YOU CAN."
/ 3 = "See above, the four categories you saw separately now appear together. Remember, each item belongs to only one group. For example, if the categories <%item.targetlabels.item(1)%> and <%item.attributelabels.item(1)%> appear on separate sides above - words meaning <%item.targetlabels.item(1)%> would go in the <%item.targetlabels.item(1)%> category, not the <%item.attributelabels.item(1)%> category. Again, the categories and key assignments for <%item.targetlabels.item(1)%> and <%item.targetlabels.item(2)%> will switch randomly between trials.

The green and white labels and items may help to identify the appropriate category. Use the left (E) and right (I) <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%>s to categorize items into four groups left and right, and correct errors by hitting the other <%expressions.buttoninstruct4%>."
</item>

<text spacebar>
/ items = ("Press the SPACE BAR to begin.")
/ position = (50%, 95%)
/ valign = bottom
</text>

****************************************************************************************************
general instruction expressions: adjust the instruction text depending on device used to run script
****************************************************************************************************
<expressions>
/buttoninstruct1 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"";} else {"Put your middle or index fingers on the E and I keys of your keyboard. ";}
/buttoninstruct2 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"response button ('E') provided on the bottom left of your screen with your left middle or index finger";} else {"(E) key";}
/buttoninstruct3 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"response button ('I') provided on the bottom right of your screen with your right middle or index finger";} else {"(I) key";}
/buttoninstruct4 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"response button";} else {"key";}
</expressions>

***********************************************************************
Performance summary
***********************************************************************

<trial summary>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	values.magnitude = "little to no";
	if( abs(expressions.d) > 0.15 ) values.magnitude = "a slight";
	if( abs(expressions.d) > 0.35 ) values.magnitude = "a moderate";
	if( abs(expressions.d) >= 0.65 ) values.magnitude = "a strong";
	if (expressions.d >= 0.0) values.preferred = item.targetlabels.1;
	if (expressions.d < 0.0) values.preferred = item.targetlabels.2;
	if (expressions.d < 0.0) values.notpreferred= item.targetlabels.1;
	if (expressions.d >= 0.0) values.notpreferred= item.targetlabels.2;
]
/ stimulustimes = [0=summary]
/ validresponse = (" ")
/ recorddata = false
</trial>

<text summary>
/ items = ("Your IAT score (D) was <% expressions.d %>, which suggests <% values.magnitude %> automatic preference for <% values.preferred %> compared to <% values.notpreferred %>.~n~n~nPress the spacebar to complete this session.") 
/ size = (60%, 60%)
/ hjustify = left
 </text>


